  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> and cut them into small bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, re-boil a kettle </p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Top, tail, peel and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-2.a-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-2.a-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-2.a-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-2.a-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-2.a-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion,</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the<strong> beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>(for a lower salt option, use half!) and add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and<strong> Henderson's Relish </strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once your <strong>vegetables</strong> have softened, add the <strong>beef mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> to the <strong>beef mince</strong> and bring to the boil</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 8-10 min or until the liquid has reduced by half – this is your <strong>beef mixture</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, grate the<strong> cheddar cheese </strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Mash until smooth – this is your <strong>creamy mashed potato</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>beef mixture</strong> has thickened, transfer it to an <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>oven-proof dish</strong></span> (or individual ones)</p>\n<p>Top the <strong>beef mixture</strong> with the <strong>creamy mashed potato</strong></p>\n<p>Sprinkle over the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p>\n<p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden brown and bubbling – this is your <strong>cottage pie </strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1784.-step-6-x400.jpg",
